#000033>(9/25/00 4:22:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Toga </span><hr size=1> I dunno about you all, but if I am in Oasis and you pull any high level mob into the path of noobies... I will kill it.  I don't care if you are kiting or what.  Everyone should know by now where to pull the lvl 35plus mobs there.  Petition me if you like, but there are many more that will agree with me doing it.  Don't pull into the noobies.<br><br>Sykoman <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uvladamir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vladamir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>n00b!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(9/26/00 5:22:58 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Toga</span><hr size=1> You are admirable for standing up to this situation DarkFaithless. It is unfortunate that we must encounter such assholes. Were the shoes on the other foot, they would be screaming for bloody murder.<br><br>Remember this Toga: What goes around comes around. ;-) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uuhgreebugga.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Uhgree Bugga</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(9/27/00 2:05:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Don't group with Toga</span><hr size=1> A chanter friend of mine partnered up with this sorry excuse of a shaman to hunt HG's in Rathe Mtns. My friend died because this idiot ignored 2 requests for SOW and never healed the chanter when he was getting whacked, even though Toga was given Clarity without asking. After the death, my friend was asked, &quot;Why didn't you zone?&quot;. Ignorance.<br><br>I grouped once with Toga before level 34 (pet level) and spent almost a half hour trying to explain a simple strategy of ping-ponging a single bard in SK. I don't know, maybe I was expected to tank while Toga nuked? Either way, that was the only and last time I group with this one.<br><br>I guess some ogres are dumber than others. ;p<br><br>Uhgree Bugga<br>34 Regent of Innoruuk<br>Elder of Chaos Plague<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udarkfaithless.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DarkFaithless</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(9/28/00 3:06:02 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Don't group with Toga</span><hr size=1> Sad to see so many ppl who have seen the same prob with this person. Don't know if the guide reported Toga or not to a GM but last I heard an actual GM was in route *like that means anything*. And Hiya Dondor. more then once have I seen you cleaning up specs while you were passing through oasis also thx for the help those couple times when I was doing the same and running lom. <br><br>And Daeon.... get some help... stay off the crack guy. Your hurting yourself and making the n00bs who look here take a second thought of getting addicted. Try some necro crack after awhile u won't think its a 100% must *do to the life loss* and maybe we can brak your habit. If any1 knows someone to help poor ole Daeon out give the guy a hand and pass him a tell. Just say /tell Daeon Lay off the Crack!   all ya gotta say whenever ya see him /giggle <p><IMG SRC=geocities.com/killerkebab/darkfaith.jpgalign=center> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udeolyenvie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deolyen Vie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/1/00 5:43:25 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Don't group with Toga</span><hr size=1> Rooted a mob she couldn't handle in between my caster and cleric last night in the Overthere.  Luckily we had the beautiful Atlanis in our group and she mezzed it before it could cause any real harm.  Now that being said I figure everyone makes mistakes so no big deal.  BUT I return to the zone today to find she has trained a ledge group like 3 times when it is so easy just to bypass the groups and run to the zone.  She intentionally runs through you instead of around you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udaeon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daeon</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/1/00 8:47:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Don't group with Toga</span><hr size=1> Just to give Toga some credit - although I disapprove of training mobs to newbies (as I stated before), she WAS in my Overthere ledge group a couple nights ago, and, when two Knights jumped myself and the cleric from behind (must've been left over from a train), I got beaten on pretty badly, especially after my first mez attempt failed.  Unconscious and a second away from dying, my life shot up out of nowhere.  I stood up, mezzed one of the knights, and the group easily took care of them.  Figuring it was the cleric, I thanked him for the save.  Then I scrolled up!  It was Toga!  I apologized whole-heartedly to Toga, thanking her very much for saving my enchanter-arse.  Dying post-hell level really would have set me back quite a bit, and she saved me a lot of time and effort.  Although she, like all of us, may have some flaws, she was with it when the going got rough.<br><br> <p>